# TB Pro Report Copy Tone

Audience: Lisa manages the support team. Reports are for ops leadership, not agent performance review.

## Do

- Explain **why** time accumulates: Pending (customer wait), Hold/Research (eng dependency), ticket mix (DNS, GH-linked bugs), wave volume.
- Lead with **business hours** (8am–8pm ET, 12h/day Zendesk schedule) for AHT, first reply, and medians.
- Show **calendar time** as secondary reference — dashed lines on charts, parenthetical notes — because subscribers experience calendar days.

## Don't

- Defensive framing about agents ("not idle agent time", "agents aren't slow", apologizing for team capacity).
- Implying blame on individual agents or naming agent performance (repo policy — never commit IC metrics).
- Leading with calendar-day AHT without business-hours context (misleading for staffing decisions).

## Scannable copy — no essay blocks

- Max ~2 short sentences per prose block OR use bullet/scan-list
- Masthead/lead: headline + metric row + one line per theme — never 80+ word paragraph
- Pattern: `.masthead__highlights`, `.scan-list` in monthly samples
- Executives/managers scan in 5 seconds — dense paragraphs fail restrained dashboard goal
- Keep numbers + push/spam/GCS honesty when splitting

## Removed sections — do not re-add without Lisa's request

- **Still open panel** — tried, then removed from launch overview (maintenance burden; doesn't scale).
- **Blocker-column pattern** — experimented in Still open table, removed with the section.

## Examples

**Good:** "39% of solves sit 3–7 business days in Pending, Research, or Snooze while eng ships fixes or customers propagate DNS."

**Good:** "Median ~3 days · business hours (8am–8pm ET)" with dashed calendar reference on trend chart.

**Avoid:** "High calendar AHT doesn't mean agents were idle — most time is Pending/Hold."
